00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:29,969
<i>I'm sure Seiji has an ideal
that he aspires to,</i>

229
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:35,040
<i>but there was something
he just couldn't express at all,</i>

230
00:14:35,107 --> 00:14:37,977
<i>and he still didn't get it
when it was said to him gently.</i>

231
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,913
<i>So, I had to take
a slightly stronger tone with him.</i>

232
00:14:41,447 --> 00:14:43,849
<i>"If you keep trying harder, you can do it.</i>

233
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:46,252
<i>I did it, so you can too."</i>

234
00:14:46,318 --> 00:14:49,755
<i>You should always think like that
when dealing with your juniors.</i>

235
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:53,459
Be more aware of the danger yourself.

236
00:14:53,525 --> 00:14:55,861
Because it's not
good enough at all right now.

237
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:58,464
You can't give an audience that.

238
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:02,735
It's your own responsibility to come up
with something you can give the audience.

239
00:15:04,603 --> 00:15:05,671
Bang, in one.

240
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:09,241
<i>They've been down this path themselves.</i>

241
00:15:10,943 --> 00:15:12,378
Louder.

242
00:15:14,813 --> 00:15:18,217
<i>That's why these sentiments
are passed down to the next generation.</i>

243
00:15:24,456 --> 00:15:25,624
MAY 3, 2012
SNOW MAN FORM

244
00:15:25,691 --> 00:15:30,095
<i>Snow Man officially became a unit
seven years ago.</i>

245
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:35,401
<i>Since then, they've performed
in every</i> Takizawa Kabuki.

246
00:15:36,201 --> 00:15:39,838
<i>It's also been
a learning opportunity for them.</i>

247
00:15:43,008 --> 00:15:45,744
<i>The biggest lesson Sakuma received
from Takizawa</i>

248
00:15:46,312 --> 00:15:48,781
<i>was about letting the audience
feel your passion.</i>

249
00:15:50,716 --> 00:15:52,618
There's lots of new ones out!

250
00:15:54,653 --> 00:15:57,156
<i>The value of an artist's passion</i>

251
00:15:57,656 --> 00:16:02,061
<i>is something Sakuma notices
especially in manga and anime.</i>

252
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:05,764
This is good. It's cute.

253
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:07,733
Here it is!

254
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:15,307
{\an8}It's a manga called
<i>Koi Wo Shiranai Bokutachi Wa</i>.

255
00:16:15,841 --> 00:16:17,476
{\an8}I really like this.

256
00:16:17,843 --> 00:16:19,411
I read <i>shoujo</i> manga.

257
00:16:21,847 --> 00:16:24,583
I don't think I have part four!
I'll get it.

258
00:16:25,517 --> 00:16:26,919
I could talk about this forever.

259
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:32,858
<i>Anime and manga make a complete
and thorough effort to entertain the fans.</i>

260
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:36,829
<i>Sakuma feels a link between this
and his own work.</i>

261
00:16:39,098 --> 00:16:45,704
The artists don't cut any corners, and put
their hearts and souls into their work.

262
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:49,575
That quality
really makes you feel something.

263
00:16:49,875 --> 00:16:56,048
They're pieces of art that are made
by lots of people working together.

264
00:16:56,849 --> 00:17:01,987
That really resonates with me
as I think about the Johnny's shows.

265
00:17:03,088 --> 00:17:06,125
If someone isn't picking up the slack,

266
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:08,360
it really doesn't sit well with me.

267
00:17:09,261 --> 00:17:14,400
If you're not constantly giving more
than 100 percent onstage,

268
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,504
I don't think you can stir
people's emotions.

269
00:17:22,641 --> 00:17:24,109
<i>So, in the end,</i>

270
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:28,714
<i>will they be able to create a show
that will stir emotions?</i>

271
00:17:33,652 --> 00:17:37,923
<i>Their three weeks of training in Tokyo
are now drawing to a close.</i>

272
00:17:46,165 --> 00:17:47,900
<i>January 31st.</i>

273
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,135
{\an8}<i>They arrive at a rainy Kyoto.</i>

274
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:52,004
{\an8}KYOTO SHIJO MINAMIZA THEATRE

275
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:55,507
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

276
00:17:55,841 --> 00:17:56,942
Good morning!

277
00:17:58,177 --> 00:17:59,211
Here we go.

278
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,848
The drums are all set up.

279
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:07,319
<i>There are three days until the show.</i>

280
00:18:07,653 --> 00:18:10,189
<i>They need to hurry to finish
the final touches.</i>

281
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:12,157
Good work! See you, then!

282
00:18:18,197 --> 00:18:19,765
I've left the box here, Sakuma.

283
00:18:22,201 --> 00:18:27,206
<i>The first thing Snow Man do after arriving
in Kyoto is set up their dressing rooms.</i>

284
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:36,115
<i>For the next month, this is home.</i>

285
00:18:37,249 --> 00:18:40,219
Time to start making my dressing room.

286
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,590
{\an8}<i>The most fastidious band member</i>

287
00:18:44,656 --> 00:18:48,227
{\an8}<i>when it comes to dressing rooms
is Watanabe.</i>

288
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:53,966
This is... What do you call this again?
Do you know?

289
00:18:54,933 --> 00:18:58,237
I hate it being here or facing this way.

290
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:04,243
I want the logo to be facing out
nice and neatly.

291
00:19:05,244 --> 00:19:07,246
<i>It seems he's the very organized type.</i>

292
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:13,185
This is the new member of the crew.
Dermatologists use it.

293
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:18,056
I sometimes bring things
they use in hospitals, too.

294
00:19:19,358 --> 00:19:22,161
<i>It's to make sure his skin
isn't dried out by the makeup.</i>

295
00:19:22,761 --> 00:19:26,265
I can't help but enjoy finding a place
for everything to go.

296
00:19:29,301 --> 00:19:35,040
<i>He has so many cosmetics because of
something he feels strongly as an idol.</i>

297
00:19:39,444 --> 00:19:44,783
Everyone has beautiful faces,
beautiful skin.

298
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:48,654
Beautiful hair.
A cool haircut and stylish clothes.

299
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:52,057
That's what people dream of.

300
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:56,762
They expect that when they come to see us.

301
00:19:56,995 --> 00:20:00,666
So, before worrying about my personality,

302
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:05,304
my top priority is to look immaculate.

303
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:09,541
As if I'm glittering.
I like to take that seriously.

304
00:20:10,309 --> 00:20:12,110
Looking to the future,

305
00:20:12,177 --> 00:20:17,583
I'd like people to see me
as the strong vocalist of Snow Man.

306
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,852
That's an accolade I aspire to.

307
00:20:21,687 --> 00:20:24,957
I'm aiming to be in that spot.

308
00:20:28,427 --> 00:20:32,864
<i>So that each of the boys' unique
characteristics can shine in the show,</i>

309
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,434
<i>the different parts have been
carefully mapped out.</i>

310
00:20:38,503 --> 00:20:40,539
{\an8}TAIKO

311
00:20:40,606 --> 00:20:43,842
{\an8}<i>A display of remarkable strength,
the taiko.</i>

312
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:49,581
{\an8}<i>TAKIZAWA KABUKI</i> SAKURA NO MAI DANCE

313
00:20:49,648 --> 00:20:51,583
{\an8}<i>A bewitching dance, portraying women.</i>

314
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,754
{\an8}Thank you ever so much!

315
00:20:57,055 --> 00:20:58,690
{\an8}<i>There are comedic parts, too.</i>

316
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:04,329
<i>Watanabe, who hopes to be
the unit's main vocalist,</i>

317
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:06,398
<i>has one solo performance.</i>

318
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:14,273
{\an8}BALLAD "MY FRIEND"

319
00:21:23,215 --> 00:21:24,616
{\an8}SWORD FIGHT (MONOCHROME)

320
00:21:24,683 --> 00:21:28,720
{\an8}<i>And doing battle in this fight scene
is Miyadate.</i>

321
00:21:29,488 --> 00:21:33,191
<i>His search to find something
only he can do brought him here.</i>

322
00:21:35,227 --> 00:21:37,195
{\an8}SHOCHIKU FILM SET, KYOTO

323
00:21:37,262 --> 00:21:39,264
{\an8}<i>They have a moment's rest in Kyoto.</i>

324
00:21:39,865 --> 00:21:42,934
{\an8}<i>Time to soak in the atmosphere
on the set of a period piece.</i>

325
00:21:45,871 --> 00:21:48,540
<i>If they don't fall completely
in love with this world,</i>

326
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:51,543
<i>the passion they need to move people
just won't be there.</i>

327
00:21:54,046 --> 00:21:57,015
QUESTION: HOW DO YOU PREPARE
TO ENTERTAIN PEOPLE?

328
00:21:57,082 --> 00:22:02,921
I think it comes down to the question
of if you can influence people or not.

329
00:22:04,189 --> 00:22:08,460
They might like your face,
the way you dance or your voice.

330
00:22:09,895 --> 00:22:11,163
That's all well and good.

331
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:15,667
But can you, this person they like,
influence people or can't you?

332
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:19,905
Will they work hard so they can see you?

333
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:23,909
Will they spend their hard-earned cash
to come to your concert?

334
00:22:24,109 --> 00:22:25,677
To see your show?

335
00:22:26,611 --> 00:22:30,048
I want to be an idol

336
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,785
who gets people to do that.

337
00:22:35,087 --> 00:22:39,424
I chose to follow this path in life,

338
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:42,694
so I absolutely don't want
to cut any corners.

339
00:22:43,495 --> 00:22:46,331
I want to see it all the way through.

340
00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:50,969
Being a part of Johnny's,
and the idol Ryota Miyadate.

341
00:22:51,636 --> 00:22:57,275
And I want people to see Ryota Miyadate
growing as an actor in a historical drama.

342
00:22:59,244 --> 00:23:02,080
{\an8}FEBRUARY 3
THE DAY OF THE OPENING PERFORMANCE

343
00:23:04,883 --> 00:23:09,755
<i>At long last,
the time has come for Snow Man.</i>

344
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:19,030
{\an8}<i>On the</i> Ride On Time <i>finale...</i>

345
00:23:19,097 --> 00:23:20,599
{\an8}Why am I doing a fake smile?

346
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:23,702
{\an8}<i>With the show imminent,</i>

347
00:23:23,769 --> 00:23:27,005
{\an8}<i>the process of trial and error
goes right up the last minute.</i>

348
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:29,174
{\an8}The collar won't stay up on this side.

349
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:32,978
{\an8}<i>It's a race against time to rehearse.</i>

350
00:23:34,279 --> 00:23:36,748
{\an8}<i>Offstage, it is like a war zone.</i>

351
00:23:37,516 --> 00:23:38,784
{\an8}My wig!

352
00:23:39,117 --> 00:23:40,152
{\an8}My wig!

353
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,788
{\an8}We're wasting time.

354
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:46,792
{\an8}<i>And an accident befalls Iwamoto.</i>

355
00:23:47,459 --> 00:23:49,294
{\an8}Now I've gone and done it.

356
00:23:51,663 --> 00:23:53,665
{\an8}<i>The first performance is finally here.</i>

357
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:59,237
<i>What will they obtain from this
incredible opportunity of a show?</i>

